                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Since writing I received<lb/> your letter please let us know how<lb/> much money it requires to put<lb/> the Synagogue &#38; burial ground<lb/> in first class order&#44; &#38; we will<lb/> pay the same this I consider<lb/> far greater charity than donate<lb/> so large a sum as Dr. Drachman<lb/> requires all your replies are held<lb/> by us strictly confidential<lb/> Yours most faithfully<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            <p>of course all<lb/> donations are &#91;&#63;&#93; from my daughter<lb/> son &#38; my self in sacred holy memory<lb/> of my late angel wife my &#38; my wife<lb/> parents<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            <p>Please let us k&#91;now&#93; &#91;... letter is cut off&#44; continues up the right side of the page&#93;</p>
            <p>german letters we receive p numbers &#38; calls &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>but one pleasing feature&#44; this entire<lb/> City rejoices at<lb/> our success<lb/> Thanks to the<lb/> God of Israel<lb/> Blessed Be His Holy<lb/> name<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Recd this from your City<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Return to ALFRED A. MARCUS &#38; Son<lb/>
                127 Dartmouth St.&#44; Hard by the Bridge&#44;<lb/>
                BOSTON&#44; Mass.<lb/>
                If not delivered within 7 days<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                P. A.<lb/></p>
            <p>546 N. 5th. c6&#47;30<lb/></p>
            </body>
